  "prompt": "What do Flipkart's delivery guys look for when I exchange my old phone for a new one?",
  "response": "When you exchange your old phone for a new one on Flipkart, the delivery executive typically checks several key aspects of your old device to ensure it matches the condition you described during the exchange process. Here's what they usually look for:\n\n1. **Physical Condition**:\n   - **Screen**: Checks for cracks, scratches, or display issues.\n   - **Body**: Looks for dents, scratches, or any physical damage.\n   - **Buttons**: Ensures all buttons (power, volume, etc.) are functional.\n\n2. **Functionality**:\n   - **Power On**: The device should turn on and boot up properly.\n   - **Touchscreen**: Verifies that the touchscreen is responsive and works without issues.\n   - **Camera**: Tests both front and rear cameras for functionality.\n   - **Battery**: Checks if the battery holds a charge and isn\u2019t swollen or damaged.\n   - **Connectivity**: Tests Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, and cellular connectivity.\n   - **Audio**: Verifies that speakers, microphone, and headphone jack (if applicable) work.\n\n3. **Accessories**:\n   - **Original Items**: Ensures the box, charger, and any other original accessories are included (if required).\n   - **SIM Tray**: Checks if the SIM tray is present and functional.\n\n4. **Software**:\n   - **Factory Reset**: Confirms that the device has been reset to factory settings.\n   - **No Lock**: Ensures the device isn\u2019t locked to a Google or iCloud account.\n\n5. **IMEI Verification**:\n   - **Matching IMEI**: Verifies that the IMEI number matches the one provided during the exchange process.\n   - **Blacklist Check**: Ensures the device isn\u2019t blacklisted or reported as stolen.\n\nIf the device meets the specified condition, the delivery executive will proceed with the exchange. If not, they might reject the exchange or adjust the exchange value accordingly based on the actual condition.",
